{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-04",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_04_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 4 - The Black Bird",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 1,
  "page_total": 7,
  "page_start_sec": 8.87,
  "page_end_sec": 252.96,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.737,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 8.87,
      "end": 10.8,
      "text": "CHAPTER FOUR THE"
    },
    {
      "start": 11.328,
      "end": 12.18,
      "text": "BLACK BIRD"
    },
    {
      "start": 14.0,
      "end": 14.78,
      "text": "Miss Wonderly,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 14.84,
      "end": 16.78,
      "text": "in a belted green crepe silk dress,"
    },
    {
      "start": 17.06,
      "end": 19.54,
      "text": "opened the door of Apartment 1001 at"
    },
    {
      "start": 19.54,
      "end": 20.06,
      "text": "the Coronet."
    },
    {
      "start": 21.06,
      "end": 22.26,
      "text": "Her face was flushed.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 22.32,
      "end": 23.8,
      "text": "Her dark red hair,"
    },
    {
      "start": 24.06,
      "end": 25.3,
      "text": "parted on the left side,"
    },
    {
      "start": 25.52,
      "end": 26.16,
      "text": "swept back"
    },
    {
      "start": 26.44,
      "end": 29.36,
      "text": "and loose waves over her right temple was somewhat tousled."
    },
    {
      "start": 30.56,
      "end": 32.02,
      "text": "Spade took off his hat and said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 32.82,
      "end": 33.42,
      "text": "\"'Good morning.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 34.44,
      "end": 36.8,
      "text": "His smile brought a fainter smile to her face.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 37.62,
      "end": 38.2,
      "text": "Her eyes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 38.32,
      "end": 39.24,
      "text": "of blue that was"
    },
    {
      "start": 39.34,
      "end": 39.92,
      "text": "almost violet,"
    },
    {
      "start": 40.12,
      "end": 41.96,
      "text": "did not lose their troubled look."
    },
    {
      "start": 43.12,
      "end": 45.46,
      "text": "She lowered her head and said in a hushed,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 45.68,
      "end": 46.1,
      "text": "timid voice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 46.24,
      "end": 47.6,
      "text": "\"'Come in,"
    },
    {
      "start": 47.64,
      "end": 47.8,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 47.88,
      "end": 48.416,
      "text": "Spade.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 49.32,
      "end": 50.76,
      "text": "She led him past the open kitchen,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 50.88,
      "end": 51.88,
      "text": "bathroom and bedroom doors"
    },
    {
      "start": 52.14,
      "end": 53.64,
      "text": "into a cream-and-red living-room,"
    },
    {
      "start": 53.8,
      "end": 55.58,
      "text": "apologizing for its confusion."
    },
    {
      "start": 57.152,
      "end": 58.34,
      "text": "\"'Everything is upside down.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 58.52,
      "end": 60.83,
      "text": "I haven't even finished unpacking.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 61.82,
      "end": 65.3,
      "text": "She laid his hat on a table and sat down on a walnut settee.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 65.984,
      "end": 69.34,
      "text": "He sat on a brocaded oval-backed chair facing her."
    },
    {
      "start": 70.42,
      "end": 71.46,
      "text": "She looked at her fingers,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 71.66,
      "end": 72.58,
      "text": "working them together,"
    },
    {
      "start": 72.68,
      "end": 73.16,
      "text": "and said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 73.72,
      "end": 74.54,
      "text": "\"'Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 74.7,
      "end": 75.04,
      "text": "Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 75.22,
      "end": 76.3,
      "text": "I've a terrible,"
    },
    {
      "start": 76.5,
      "end": 77.92,
      "text": "terrible confession to make.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 77.94,
      "end": 77.98,
      "text": "week."
    },
    {
      "start": 79.264,
      "end": 82.96,
      "text": "Spade smiled a polite smile which she did not raise her eyes to",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 82.96,
      "end": 84.24,
      "text": "see and said nothing."
    },
    {
      "start": 85.22,
      "end": 86.1,
      "text": "\"'That...",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 86.1,
      "end": 89.0,
      "text": "that story I told you yesterday was all..."
    },
    {
      "start": 89.0,
      "end": 90.74,
      "text": "a story,' she"
    },
    {
      "start": 90.82,
      "end": 94.34,
      "text": "stammered and looked up at him now with miserable frightened eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 95.0,
      "end": 95.82,
      "text": "\"'Oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 95.82,
      "end": 97.5,
      "text": "that,' Spade said lightly."
    },
    {
      "start": 98.46,
      "end": 99.86,
      "text": "\"'We didn't exactly believe your",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 99.94,
      "end": 100.512,
      "text": "story.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 101.6,
      "end": 105.76,
      "text": "Then perplexity was added to the misery and fright in her eyes.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 106.7,
      "end": 109.184,
      "text": "We believe you're two hundred dollars.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 110.42,
      "end": 111.0,
      "text": "\"'You mean—'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 112.04,
      "end": 113.98,
      "text": "She seemed to have no idea of what he meant.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 115.616,
      "end": 118.88,
      "text": "\"'I mean that you paid us more than if you'd been telling the truth,'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 119.54,
      "end": 120.6,
      "text": "he explained blandly."
    },
    {
      "start": 121.696,
      "end": 123.59,
      "text": "\"'And enough more to make it all right.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 124.256,
      "end": 126.28,
      "text": "Her eyes lighted up suddenly."
    },
    {
      "start": 127.08,
      "end": 129.14,
      "text": "She lifted herself a few inches from the settee,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 129.32,
      "end": 130.3,
      "text": "settled down again,"
    },
    {
      "start": 130.66,
      "end": 131.7,
      "text": "smoothed her skirt,"
    },
    {
      "start": 131.9,
      "end": 132.7,
      "text": "leaned forward,"
    },
    {
      "start": 132.88,
      "end": 134.14,
      "text": "and spoke eagerly."
    },
    {
      "start": 135.34,
      "end": 137.1,
      "text": "And even now you'd be willing to?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 138.336,
      "end": 140.9,
      "text": "Spade stopped her with a palm-up motion of one hand.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 141.42,
      "end": 143.34,
      "text": "The upper part of his face frowned."
    },
    {
      "start": 143.82,
      "end": 144.74,
      "text": "The lower part smiled."
    },
    {
      "start": 146.432,
      "end": 146.9,
      "text": "That depends,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 147.38,
      "end": 147.9,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 149.04,
      "end": 149.86,
      "text": "The hell of it is,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 149.98,
      "end": 150.18,
      "text": "miss."
    },
    {
      "start": 150.86,
      "end": 152.68,
      "text": "Is your name Wonderly or LeBlanc?"
    },
    {
      "start": 153.98,
      "end": 155.04,
      "text": "She blushed and murmured,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 156.16,
      "end": 157.18,
      "text": "It's O'Shaughnessy.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 157.792,
      "end": 158.68,
      "text": "Bridget O'Shaughnessy."
    },
    {
      "start": 160.34,
      "end": 161.16,
      "text": "The hell of it is,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 161.16,
      "end": 161.79,
      "text": "Miss O'Shaughnessy,"
    },
    {
      "start": 162.66,
      "end": 163.62,
      "text": "that a couple of murders",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 164.0,
      "end": 165.1,
      "text": "She winced."
    },
    {
      "start": 165.792,
      "end": 166.88,
      "text": "\"'Coming together like this,"
    },
    {
      "start": 166.92,
      "end": 168.22,
      "text": "get everybody stirred up."
    },
    {
      "start": 168.88,
      "end": 170.7,
      "text": "Make the police think they can go the limits."
    },
    {
      "start": 171.34,
      "end": 173.54,
      "text": "Make everything and everybody hard to handle."
    },
    {
      "start": 173.98,
      "end": 174.96,
      "text": "And expensive.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 176.032,
      "end": 176.62,
      "text": "\"'It's not—'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 177.28,
      "end": 179.88,
      "text": "He stopped talking because she had stopped listening"
    },
    {
      "start": 180.14,
      "end": 182.22,
      "text": "and was impatiently waiting for him to finish."
    },
    {
      "start": 183.42,
      "end": 184.3,
      "text": "\"'Mr.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 184.42,
      "end": 184.74,
      "text": "Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 184.92,
      "end": 186.3,
      "text": "tell me the truth.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 186.74,
      "end": 189.42,
      "text": "Her voice quivered on the verge of hysteria."
    },
    {
      "start": 189.9,
      "end": 192.58,
      "text": "Her face had become haggard around desperate eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 194.18,
      "end": 195.72,
      "text": "Am I to blame for...",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 196.26,
      "end": 197.13,
      "text": "for last night?'"
    },
    {
      "start": 198.208,
      "end": 199.16,
      "text": "Spade shook his head.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 200.44,
      "end": 203.18,
      "text": "\"'Not unless there are things I don't know about,' he said.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 204.2,
      "end": 206.02,
      "text": "\"'You warned us that Thursby was dangerous.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 206.86,
      "end": 207.38,
      "text": "Of course,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 207.38,
      "end": 209.52,
      "text": "you did lie to us about your sister and all,"
    },
    {
      "start": 209.96,
      "end": 210.88,
      "text": "but that doesn't count."
    },
    {
      "start": 211.66,
      "end": 212.736,
      "text": "We didn't believe you.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 213.44,
      "end": 215.34,
      "text": "He shrugged his sloping shoulders."
    },
    {
      "start": 216.78,
      "end": 218.8,
      "text": "\"'I wouldn't say it looked like your fault.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 219.82,
      "end": 220.24,
      "text": "She said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 221.088,
      "end": 221.56,
      "text": "\"'Thank you,'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 222.112,
      "end": 222.7,
      "text": "very softly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 223.04,
      "end": 225.4,
      "text": "and then moved her head from side to side."
    },
    {
      "start": 226.58,
      "end": 228.38,
      "text": "But I'll always blame myself.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 229.96,
      "end": 231.36,
      "text": "She put a hand to her throat.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 232.34,
      "end": 233.06,
      "text": "Mr.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 233.2,
      "end": 236.32,
      "text": "Archer was so—so alive yesterday afternoon,"
    },
    {
      "start": 236.92,
      "end": 238.54,
      "text": "so solid and hearty,"
    },
    {
      "start": 238.54,
      "end": 239.22,
      "text": "and—"
    },
    {
      "start": 239.552,
      "end": 240.02,
      "text": "Stop it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 240.14,
      "end": 241.0,
      "text": "Slade commanded."
    },
    {
      "start": 241.62,
      "end": 242.98,
      "text": "He knew what he was doing."
    },
    {
      "start": 243.7,
      "end": 244.96,
      "text": "There are the chances we'd take."
    },
    {
      "start": 246.42,
      "end": 247.72,
      "text": "Was—was he married?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 248.38,
      "end": 248.9,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 249.08,
      "end": 250.32,
      "text": "with ten thousand insurance,"
    },
    {
      "start": 250.74,
      "end": 252.96,
      "text": "no children and a wife who didn't like him."
    }
  ]
}